$ SSL/TSL

→ development/security/cryptography/SSL and development/security/cryptography/TLS provide authentication and encryption over insecure networks.

{ History

  SSL is called → development/security/cryptography/TLS since version 3. (SSL 1.0 -> SSL 2.0 -> SSL 3.0 -> TLS 1.0 -> TLS 1.1 -> TLS 1.2). TLS 1.0 sometimes called SSL 3.1.

}
